<br>
Alas...<br>
<br>
Truly the majority of those who play on this server, are, in the best sense of the word, honorable.  Again, with that said, where is the honor in not respecting this type of system?  I have full intention of building (and am making fabulous progress) a guild capable of performing planer raids or large game hunts in a closed raid fashion with relative ease.  With that said, I can assure everyone that while I am at the helm of Chivalrous Valor, we will continue to respect the system that has been established by the *majority* of the playing guilds on this server.  It would be dishonorable, in my opinion, to not do so.<br>
<br>
This entire discussion seems bullish to me.  It seems that the top 10 guilds in terms of raw power prefer the FCFS system while the rest of us are screaming for mercy.  I admire those of you in the power guilds that have posted on this thread and stated explicitly that you left raid targets up for reasonable intent.  That is honorable. And for those of you who continue to wipe zones despite intents posted on this thread...  it speaks volumes of your integrity...<br>
<br>
I'm sure that a compromise can be reached... and from what I have seen on this server (relatively new to FV), a compromise is desperately needed.  And why not?  I have raised many characters across many servers and reservation systems are *preferred* for the very reasons the majority of us are stating...  Us &quot;little guys&quot; like to have fun too. :/<br>
<br>
<br>
