<br>
1-Almost every guild will respect an Open Raid attempting to do something.<br>
There is NO such thing as a Semi-Open Raid. It isn't open to all, then it's limited, and you roll your dice and move your mice like everybody else.<br>
<br>
2-It has happened, but it is very rare, where one guild will leapfrog another about to hit a mob. (F&amp;F and Reso ganking each other does not count) See the Turtle thread, circa 14 months ago or so. Most will even give you another shot if you wipe the first time. Two strikes and you are out though. This ain't baseball and not your Aunt Peggy's....you don't get three strikes, or as much as you want. One wipe might happen because of luck, after that, it's seen as a lack of power, tactics, leadership, you name it. Nobody is obligated to watch an underpowered, poorly lead, can't get it's act together force die 20 times against a mob that it is ready and able to take out. Go back to Double AA, learn what you are doing, then come back. And don't whine about it either.<br>
<br>
3-Not everybody knows every frigging spawn time or rate of every mob in the game. Sometimes people kill things, not knowing that it is a 72 hour spawn or what have you.....which<br>
leads to reason 4.<br>
<br>
4-Not everybody reads the board. Not everybody KNOWS about this board. If there is an official board, I would guess it would be Sony's FV Board, and not this one. I am almost certain that my entire guild does not read this particular section after getting ganked twice. (I posted and helped organize the Infamous Fear Raid that Vulrath and Shabba speak of) We are an Iksar orientated guild. Goodies don't want us, Evil's can't handle our neutrals. If it isn't a raid we plan or are specificly invited too, we just don't go, so why should we bother reading this section?<br>
<br>
5-Grow up. Learn to  have Alternate plans. Have some ideas of what ya'd like to do, and then back ups for them too. My guild might be the second worst travelling guild on FV (Wave to the Ven Sho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Go Team!! You're #1!!). We have one wizard and one druid on with any regularity. That means we run and PoK and run some more. If we can do it, and I can run raids with Team A.D.D. then so can every single guild on this server.<br>
<br>
6- Talk to the &quot;High End&quot; guilds. For the most part if you need help with &quot;an&quot; item, one or two of the members might be bored and can come around to help, and this will assure that they know that Epic_Mob_02 is being hunted on Tuesday, so please, Clan Resolute Storms of Demented Twisted Fury, don't have one of your single group Kill Teams go and stomp on it. (However this sometimes involves curious bargains such as &quot;Um sure Milow, you can tank if you want&quot; )<br>
